Class AirlineManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.lexicon.utilities.AirlineManager

  • public class AirlineManager

      • addAirplane

        public void addAirplane(Airplane airplane)
        Adds an Airplane object to the AirlineManager's list of airplanes.
        Parameters:
        airplane - the Airplane object to add.

      • removeAirplane

        public boolean removeAirplane(int airplaneIndex)
        Removes the airplane corresponding to the parameter airplaneIndex from the AirlineManager's list of airplanes. Returns true if successful and returns false if no plane corresponding to airplaneIndex was found.
        Parameters:
        airplaneIndex - the index corresponding to the Airplane to remove.
        Returns:
        true if successful and false if no plane corresponding to airplaneIndex was found.

      • hasAvailibleSeat

        public boolean hasAvailibleSeat(java.lang.String airplane,
                                SeatType seatType)
        Checks if any Airplane (for which the toString method returns a String equal to the given airplane argument) has at least one available seat of seatType.
        Parameters:
        airplane - a String matching the toString result of the desired Airplane object.
        seatType - The seat type of the checked for seat. Can be either ECONOMY_SEAT or BUSINESS_SEAT.
        Returns:
        true if a matching Airplane has available seats and false otherwise.

      • getAvailibleFlights

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> getAvailibleFlights()
        Checks which Airplane objects are available for flight.
        Returns:
        an ArrayList of toString results for each available airplane.

      • addReservation

        public int addReservation(java.lang.String airplane,
                          java.lang.String name,
                          SeatType seatType,
                          java.util.Map<FoodItem,java.lang.Integer> foodMap)
        Attempts to add a reservation to one Airplane.The foodMap parameter should consist of a map between FoodItems and the desired number of that FoodItem. Returns Booking ID if successful. Returns a negative number if the reservation failed.
        Parameters:
        airplane - a String equal to the toString result for the desired Airplane object.
        name - the name of the one making the reservation.
        seatType - the seat type of the reservation. Can be either ECONOMY_SEAT or BUSINESS_SEAT.
        foodMap - a map between FoodItems and the ordered number of that FoodItem.
        Returns:
        the booking ID (which is a positive integer) if successful and a negative number if the reservation failed.

      • removeReservation

        public boolean removeReservation(int bookingID)
        Attempts to remove a reservation.
        Parameters:
        bookingID - the booking ID of the reservation to be removed.
        Returns:
        true if the reservation was found and removed. False if the reservation wasn't found.

      • getMenu

        public FoodItem[] getMenu(SeatType seatType)
        Returns a menu corresponding to a seat type.
        Parameters:
        seatType - the seat type for the sought menu. Can be either ECONOMY_SEAT or BUSINESS_SEAT.
        Returns:
        an array of FoodItems.

      • getIncome

        public double getIncome()
        Calculates the total income of the AirlineManager.
        Returns:
        a double containing the calculated income.

      • getProfit

        public double getProfit()
        Calculates the total profit of the AirlineManager. The profit is equal to 30% of the AirlineManager's income.
        Returns:
        a double containing the calculated profit.

      • getSeatPrice

        public double getSeatPrice(SeatType seatType)
        Returns the price of a seat.
        Parameters:
        seatType - the seat type for which to get the price. Can be either ECONOMY_SEAT or BUSINESS_SEAT.
        Returns:
        a double containing the price of the seat.
